It was good to be safely back in her quiet secret haven. The past few months had been a bit hard. Usually Prophet was the protector and care giver. Here in Santa Carla, she had been left to her own devices quite a bit.<br>
And now she was supposed to represent the Family. She giggled maniacally and accidentally pulled the head off of a stuffed animal... but it wasn’t one she cared about. Cybel focused by working on her latest security hack. Should she actually try to take care of this strange motley group she was supposed to speak for? Should she act only to take care of herself and her brother? Were those two things mutually exclusive or inclusive? She was very confused, years of scrabbling to survive as they could, had not given her much socialization.<br>
And Santa Carla was just ass-backwards as well. The very chaos that allowed her and Prophet to settle in, also gave Cybel none of the structure and politics she was used to having to survive against.<br>
“Hey Sis, let’s go hunting.” Prophet’s rough voice rasped over the intercom. There was another thing to get used to. Her brother’s speaking didn’t seem to attract as much notice as it should. No one in this City paid attention to the things that seemed important everywhere else...<br>
But hunting, hunting would be a welcome distraction to having to play grownup games. Cybel checked her work, set her security systems and went to the door. She pulled on her coat and put on her mask and hat and ventured out. <br>
